description:
&lt;p&gt;A great opportunity is available for a suitably experienced Speech and Language Therapist with skills in working with primary aged students. You will join our large, well-established schools team to provide a service to students attending both primary schools. Working collaboratively with school staff, you will provide a high quality service to students with significant language and communication difficulties. You will be involved in providing training, planning and jointly running groups and working closely with school staff to facilitate the inclusion of students with speech, language and communication needs. We can offer:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;• A team base with other SLTs and multi-disciplinary colleagues &lt;br /&gt;• Regular team meetings&lt;br /&gt;• Access to clinical specialists for second opinions/support&lt;br /&gt;• Admin support&lt;br /&gt;• Opportunities for continuous professional development through a range of learning experiences including opportunities to shadow colleagues&lt;br /&gt;• Time for reflective practice&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;For further details / informal visits contact:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;NameFiona WeirJob titlePrincipal Speech and Language TherapistTelephone number020 8736 7101Additional contact information&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Fiona Weir - Principal Speech and Language Therapist on 020 8736 7101&lt;/p&gt;
